President Donald J. Trump commends the Senate Finance Committee for introducing their version of the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, stating that it is a significant step towards providing tax relief for the American people. He is pleased with the unity displayed by the House and Senate in their efforts to deliver tax relief for the middle class, simplify the tax code, and support American businesses. The President intends to work with Congress to ensure that tax cuts and reforms are implemented by the end of the year.